name: citric acid production | maize starch | Cutoff, S
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/2605/documentation

Citric acid is produced by a fermentation process which employs a strain of the micro-organism Aspergillus niger to convert carbohydrate into citric acid: The substrate is heat treated and inoculated with Aspergillus niger. After the fermentation the biological solids (mycelium) are removed. Then citric acid is recovered from the remaining broth and the resulting citric acid solution is purified by ion exchange and carbon treatment. Finally the solution is evaporated, and citric acid is crystallised, dried, sieved and packaged. 

From cradle, i.e. including all upstream activities.

Production of citric acid including materials and energy uses, waste production and emissions. Infrastructure is estimated.
category: C:Manufacturing/20:Manufacture of chemicals and chemical products/201:Manufacture of basic chemicals, fertilizers and nitrogen compounds, plastics/2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals

processDocumentation.timeDescription: According to producer data is valid for at least another 2 years until 2013.
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data from citric acid production in China, used as Global average, as more than 50% of global production volume is produced in China
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Data were derived from a detailed cost calculation of a planned, but not built production plant in the region of Jilin, China.
